‹ Back to Our Businesses


 




 

GulfstreamGulfstream Aerospace Corporation engineers, manufactures and services the world’s most technologically advanced business-jet aircraft. We have produced more than 2,500 aircraft for customers around the world since the 1958 debut of the Gulfstream I, the world’s first purpose-built business aircraft.
We offer a comprehensive fleet of aircraft, comprising the G150, the G280, the G450, the G550, the G500, the G600, the G650 and the G650ER. 
Engineering and Research
Gulfstream designs and develops aircraft at our Savannah Research and Development Center. The five-building campus houses engineers and support staff integral to the research, testing and development of current and future Gulfstream aircraft. Gulfstream has the only hemi-anechoic acoustic test facility used in the development of business aircraft.
Manufacturing
Gulfstream manufactures large and ultra-large aircraft at our Savannah, Georgia, headquarters. Gulfstream holds a Federal Aviation Administration Production Certificate, counts more than 900 Lean Specialist trainees among our employees and offers courses in more than 15 different processes and tools focused on Lean and other sustainability initiatives.
Completions
Gulfstream offers a wide array of cabin configurations. We outfit cabins, paint the exteriors and install avionics equipment upgrades at our completion centers in Appleton, Wisconsin; Brunswick, Georgia; Dallas, Texas; Long Beach, California; and Savannah, Georgia. We complete mid-cabin aircraft at our facility in Dallas.
Product Support
Gulfstream operates the largest factory-owned service network in the business aviation industry. The support system is anchored by 11 service centers located on four continents, including the world’s largest purpose-built business aircraft maintenance facility, which is in Savannah. Gulfstream is the first manufacturer to open a service facility on mainland China at Beijing Capital International Airport. Gulfstream also offers Field and Airborne Support Teams (FAST), with ground support vehicles and aircraft to perform service remotely.
Sales and Design
Gulfstream coordinates aircraft purchases and plans cabin furnishings with buyers at Sales and Design Centers in Savannah, Dallas, Long Beach, and London, England.


 



 



 







Gulfstream Website ›Corporate Headquarters: 500 Gulfstream RoadSavannah, GA 31408United StatesPhone: 1-800-810-4853 (GULF)Founded: 1958Facts: Gulfstream GI made its first flight in 1958.
GD acquired Gulfstream in 1999.
In 2013, the Gulfstream G650 set world speed record for westbound, around-the-world flight in 41 hours, 7 minutes.
Gulfstream has been awarded the prestigious Collier Trophy three times: in 1997 for the Gulfstream V; in 2003 for the G550; and in 2014 G650.
Our service network has more than $1.4 billion in parts inventory positioned at strategic locations around the world.

  



 




 
