General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE:GD) Stake Raised by Parallel Advisors LLC
28 July 2017



Finally, Central Bank & Trust Co. increased its stake in shares of General Dynamics Corporation by 33.9% in the first quarter. Following the sale, the director now directly owns 7,336 shares of the company's stock, valued at approximately $1,437,929.36.Other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently bought and sold shares of the company. NC now owns 6,010 shares of the aerospace company's stock worth $1,125,000 after buying an additional 70 shares during the period. Davis R M Inc. raised its stake in shares of General Dynamics Corporation by 8.0% in the first quarter. Moreover, Agran Libbie has 0.06% invested in General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE:GD) for 1,350 shares. Central Bank & Trust Co. now owns 872 shares of the aerospace company's stock worth $164,000 after buying an additional 221 shares during the last quarter. Cullen Frost Bankers Incorporated holds 0.09% of its portfolio in General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE:GD) for 14,457 shares. Beacon Financial Group now owns 8,143 shares of the aerospace company's stock worth $1,537,000 after buying an additional 766 shares during the period. Institutional investors own 86.80% of the company's stock. The stock of General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE:GD) earned "Outperform" rating by RBC Capital Markets on Thursday, January 12. BidaskClub lowered General Dynamics Corporation from a "strong-buy" recommendation to a "buy" recommendation in a analysis note on Sunday, Jul 16th. The firm has a market capitalization of $58.74 billion, a PE ratio of 19.52 and a beta of 0.72. The Stock becomes significant when you consider how many shares are shorted versus the average daily volume, means how many days to cover those short shares at that volume.General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE:GD) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Wednesday, July 26th. The company reported the earnings of $2.45/Share in the last quarter where the estimated EPS by analysts was $2.43/share.


