Stock to watch: General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE: GD)



































































FXDailyReport.Com











Stock to watch: General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE: GD)


 By

Swapna Meka

July 26, 2017,  3:15 pm

 •  Posted in Companies, Stocks









General Dynamics Corporation (NYSE: GD) stock lost over 4.8% as the group reported a weak top line in their second quarter of 2017 results. The group’s revenues lost over 1.3% to $7.675 billion in the second quarter of 2017 as compared to $7.774 billion in the prior corresponding period.
On the other hand, the group’s operating margin enhanced 60 basis-point to 13.8 percent during the second quarter of 2017 against 13.2% in the prior corresponding period.
Net cash provided by operating activities in the quarter totaled $477 million, up 21 percent from the year ago quarter. The group’s overall backlog reached $58.6 billion during the second-quarter of 2017, driven by the order activity across the Gulfstream product portfolio coupled with better demand across defense products, including another quarter of a book-to-bill ratio (orders divided by revenue) greater than one-to-one in the Information Systems and Technology group. The group forecasts this contract value to be $24.4 billion. Overall potential contract value, which is the sum of all backlog components, is $83 billion at the end of the quarter.




General Dynamics Corporation even enhanced their EPS forecasts to $9.70 – $9.75 as compared to $9.50 – $9.55. GD bought back 2.7 million of their outstanding shares during the quarter and an overall of 4.6 million outstanding shares in this year to date. Cash from operating activities enhanced 21% yoy to $477 million, as compared to the same period of last year. Free cash flow from operations reached $386 million.
Meanwhile, Matthew Goff Investment Advisor bought a stake in the group in the first quarter, acquiring 17,612 shares valued at over $3,297,000. Citizens Financial Group enhanced their stake in the group by 0.1% during the first quarter, while the fund has 72,140 shares of the group. As per the Citizens Financial Group filing, they have a worth of over $13,505,000 of the group’s shares.
General Dynamics Corporation stock rallied over 12.2% rose over 12.2% in this year to date (as of 10:01AM EDT; Source: Google finance). General Dynamics stock has “Strong Buy” as per nine analysts consensus ratings, based on tipranks.com. The stock has a consensus target price of over $216.63, which is over 10.8% upside from the current levels.








 






